#Print out descriptive statistics for a selection of quantitative and categorical variables ##Quantitative variables cereal calories

class(df$calories)
## [1] "integer"
summary(df$calories)
##    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
##    50.0   100.0   110.0   106.9   110.0   160.0
hist(df$calories,
     main="Histgram for calories",
     xlab="calories",
     border = "darkgreen",
     col = "lightgreen",
     xlim = c(50,130),
     ylab = "The frequancy of calories",
     las=1,
     breaks = 10)

##Categorical variables cereal manufacture

class(df$mfr)
## [1] "character"
table(df$mfr)
## 
##  A  G  K  N  P  Q  R 
##  1 22 23  6  9  8  8
mypct= round((table(df$mfr))/(sum(table(df$mfr)))*100)
lbls=paste(names(table(df$mfr)),mypct,"%")
pie(table(df$mfr),lbls,main = "pie chart of manufacture")
